S1-T03: IAM policies, cost optimization, and Well-Architected review
Completed: 2026-04-05
Agent: aws-specialist

Deliverables:
- docs/aws/iam-policies.md — Exact IAM policy JSON for redirect/api/worker Lambda roles, trust policies, Terraform HCL implementation, permission matrix, security audit checklist
- docs/aws/cost-optimization.md — Monthly cost breakdown at 1K/10K/50K RPS across 10 AWS services, 9 optimization strategies (SQS batching, WAF scoping, click aggregation, Savings Plans, reserved capacity, log retention, X-Ray sampling, CloudFront caching, ElastiCache RI), optimized totals showing 60-64% savings
- docs/aws/well-architected.md — 5-pillar review with 16 prioritized findings, top 5 pre-launch actions, gap analysis with remediation plans

Key findings:
- SQS FIFO and WAF Bot Control are the top cost drivers at scale (combined $80K/month at 10K RPS unoptimized)
- SQS batch operations + WAF scoping alone save ~$71K/month at 10K RPS
- DynamoDB Global Tables not yet configured (reliability gap for RPO < 1 min target)
- Redis AUTH token rotation not automated (security gap)
- No k6 baseline load test results documented (performance gap)
